"Mannstein H., Spichtinger P., Gierens K.","A note on how to avoid contrail cirrus",2005,"Transportation Research Part D: Transport and Environment","10","5",,"421","426",,,10.1016/j.trd.2005.04.012,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-22544444223&partnerID=40&md5=c0054cecf5c86a39a0928bc7661b8b8e","Deutsches Zentrum für Luft- und Raumfahrt, Institut für Physik der Atmosphäre, Oberpfaffenhofen, 82230 Weßling, Germany","Mannstein, H., Deutsches Zentrum für Luft- und Raumfahrt, Institut für Physik der Atmosphäre, Oberpfaffenhofen, 82230 Weßling, Germany; Spichtinger, P., Deutsches Zentrum für Luft- und Raumfahrt, Institut für Physik der Atmosphäre, Oberpfaffenhofen, 82230 Weßling, Germany; Gierens, K., Deutsches Zentrum für Luft- und Raumfahrt, Institut für Physik der Atmosphäre, Oberpfaffenhofen, 82230 Weßling, Germany","Aircraft induced cirrus clouds have a major effect on climate. Here we use operational radiosonde data with high vertical resolution to estimate the effect of a small change in flight altitudes on the contrail and cirrus formation. It is shown that a substantial fraction of contrails and contrail induced cirrus can be avoided by relatively small changes in flight level, due to the shallowness of ice-super-saturation layers. © 2005 Elsevier Ltd. All rights reserved.","Cloud formation; Contrails; Global warming","Air transportation; Climate change; Clouds; Flight dynamics; Radiosondes; Cirrus formation; Flight altitudes; Ice-super-saturation layers; Vertical resolution; Aircraft; cirrus; contrail",,,,,,"Appleman, H., The formation of exhaust condensation trails by jet aircraft (1953) Bulletin of the American Meteorological Society, 34, pp. 14-20; Fichter, C., Marquart, S., Sausen, R., Lee, D.S., Norman, P.D., Impact of cruise altitude on contrails (2004) Aviation, Atmosphere and Climate. Proceedings of a European Conference, , Sausen, R., Fichter, C., Amanatidis, G., (Eds.) European Commission, Air Pollution Research Report 83, Brussels; 